<% content_for :title, "Select Link" %>

<div class="content-spacing">

  <p>Select links convert <code>select</code> elements in to linkable objects:</p>

  <p>
    <select data-select-link class="form--medium">
      <option value="">Select a page...</option>
      <option value="http://google.com.au">Google</option>
      <option value="http://katalyst.com.au">Visit the Katalyst Website</option>
    </select>
  </p>

  <p>All you need to do to make this happen is add <code>data-select-link</code> on your select element, then use the URLs as the <code>value</code> for each <code>option</code>.</p>

  <pre class="sg-pre prettyprint">&lt;select data-select-link class="form--medium">
  &lt;option value="">Select a page...&lt;/option>
  &lt;option value="http://google.com.au">Google&lt;/option>
  &lt;option value="http://katalyst.com.au">Visit the Katalyst Website&lt;/option>
&lt;/select></pre>

  <p>If the select contains a link that matches the URL of the page the user is currently on, it will automatically make that one selected on page load. This is helpful if using it as a navigation tool:</p>

  <p>
    <select data-select-link class="form--medium">
      <option value="">Select a page...</option>
      <option value="http://google.com.au">Google</option>
      <option value="http://google.com.au">Google</option>
      <option value="http://google.com.au">Google</option>
      <option value="<%= request.path -%>"><%= request.path -%></option>
      <option value="http://google.com.au">Google</option>
    </select>
  </p>

</div>
